To draw a chessboard in LaTeX using a FEN (Forsyth-Edwards Notation) string, you can use the `chessboard` package. Below is an example of how you can create a LaTeX document that includes the necessary commands and packages to display a chessboard from a given FEN string.

First, ensure you have the `chessboard` package installed. Then, you can use the following LaTeX code:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chessboard}
\usepackage{chessfss}

\begin{document}

% Example FEN string: rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1
% This represents the initial position of a chess game.

\newcommand{\drawchessboard}[1]{
  \chessboard[setfen=#1]
}

\section*{Chessboard from FEN}

% Replace the FEN string below with your desired FEN string
\drawchessboard{rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1}

\end{document}
```

In this code:
- The `chessboard` package is used to draw the chessboard.
- The `chessfss` package is used for chess fonts and symbols.
- The `\drawchessboard` command is defined to take a FEN string as an argument and draw the corresponding chessboard.
- The `\chessboard[setfen=#1]` command within `\drawchessboard` sets the FEN string and draws the board.

Replace the FEN string in the `\drawchessboard` command with your desired FEN string to display the corresponding chessboard state.

Compile this LaTeX document with a LaTeX editor that supports the `chessboard` package, such as Overleaf or a local LaTeX installation with the necessary packages.

